<subSubSection id="EBCDF5AB7735FFF4FF4EF9890F614D3E" pageId="14" pageNumber="395" type="description">
<paragraph id="A368A6207735FFF4FF4EF9890ABA4C35" blockId="14.[151,687,1547,1610]" box="[151,395,1584,1610]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57735FFF4FF4EF9890A2F4C35" box="[151,286,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–47" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1997,2021]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,535,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-133@11.[174,1412,525,1974]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–47. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404167/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Figs. 46–47</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57735FFF4FEF0F9890ABA4C35" box="[297,395,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">200–203</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A368A6207735FFF4FF4EF9CB09D84CCE" blockId="14.[151,1437,1650,2037]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis id="91A37A327735FFF4FF4EF9CB0A184CF3" bold="true" box="[151,297,1650,1676]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Description.</emphasis>
Pale brown, yellowish or greenish, often with variable dark pattern on head, pro-, and mesonotum (
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57735FFF4FF46F92E0A184CCD" box="[159,297,1687,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–47" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1997,2021]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,535,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-133@11.[174,1412,525,1974]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–47. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404167/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Figs. 46–47</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with distinct median carina.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A368A6207735FFF4FF1EF9020E654D62" blockId="14.[151,1437,1650,2037]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
Abdominal apodemes of 2 
<superScript id="54A20B687735FFF4FE36F9030ACE4CB7" attach="left" box="[495,511,1722,1736]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">nd</superScript>
tergite in male long, narrow triangular, separated by oval notch (
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57735FFF4FB0EF9020E0B4CAA" box="[1239,1338,1723,1749]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Fig. 201</figureCitation>
). Sternal apodemes of similar shape, but wider and shorter, separated by wide notch (
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57735FFF4FC08F9660F004C86" box="[977,1073,1759,1785]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Fig. 202</figureCitation>
). Penis stem in side view narrow, evenly bent at almost right angle (
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57735FFF4FDD2F8BA095A4D62" box="[523,619,1795,1821]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Fig. 200</figureCitation>
). 2 
<superScript id="54A20B687735FFF4FD52F8BB09AA4D6F" attach="left" box="[651,667,1794,1808]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">nd</superScript>
valvulae of ovipositor with 2–3 preapical teeth each (
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57735FFF4FB3EF8BA0E764D62" box="[1255,1351,1795,1821]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Fig. 203</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A368A6207735FFF4FF1EF89E0F614D3E" blockId="14.[151,1437,1650,2037]" box="[199,1104,1830,1858]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
